{
  "mcpServers": {
    "filesystem-bridge": {
      "command": "node",
      "args": ["/ABSOLUTE/PATH/TO/claude-desktop-mcp-bridge/dist/filesystem-bridge/server.js"],
      "env": {
        "ALLOWED_PATHS": "/Users/yourname/projects,/Users/yourname/Documents",
        "READ_ONLY": "false",
        "MAX_FILE_SIZE": "10485760"
      }
    },
    "shell-bridge": {
      "command": "node",
      "args": ["/ABSOLUTE/PATH/TO/claude-desktop-mcp-bridge/dist/shell-bridge/server.js"],
      "env": {
        "TIMEOUT": "120000",
        "ALLOWED_COMMANDS": "ls,pwd,cd,cat,grep,find,git,npm,node,python",
        "BLOCKED_COMMANDS": "rm,rmdir,del,format,fdisk,sudo"
      }
    }
  }
}

/*
Claude Desktop MCP Configuration Guide:

IMPORTANT: You MUST use absolute paths in the "args" field!

1. Build the MCP servers first:
   npm install && npm run build

2. Get the absolute path to this project:
   pwd  # or echo $PWD (Unix) / cd (Windows)

3. Find your Claude Desktop config file:
   - macOS: ~/Library/Application Support/Claude/claude_desktop_config.json
   - Windows: %APPDATA%\Claude\claude_desktop_config.json
   - Linux: ~/.config/Claude/claude_desktop_config.json

4. Replace "/ABSOLUTE/PATH/TO/claude-desktop-mcp-bridge" with your actual path

5. Update ALLOWED_PATHS to your project directories

6. Restart Claude Desktop

7. The new tools should appear in your conversation:
   - read_file, write_file, edit_file, glob_search (filesystem operations)
   - run_command, run_background, get_current_directory, change_directory (shell operations)

Example absolute paths:
- Unix: "/home/user/projects/claude-desktop-mcp-bridge/dist/filesystem-bridge/server.js"
- Windows: "C:\\Users\\user\\projects\\claude-desktop-mcp-bridge\\dist\\filesystem-bridge\\server.js"

Security Notes:
- ALLOWED_PATHS: Comma-separated list of directories the filesystem bridge can access
- READ_ONLY: Set to "true" to disable write operations
- ALLOWED_COMMANDS: Whitelist specific commands (optional)
- BLOCKED_COMMANDS: Always block dangerous commands like rm, format, etc.

Troubleshooting:
- If tools don't appear: Check Claude Desktop logs for MCP server startup errors
- If paths fail: Ensure all paths are absolute, not relative
- If commands fail: Check BLOCKED_COMMANDS list and file permissions
*/